General Motors Co To Cut 20 Executive Jobs In Product Development Revamp-Reuters
Wednesday, 25 Jul 2012 02:12pm EDT
Reuters reported that General Motors Co will cut 20 executive jobs in global product development in a restructuring. The changes, effective August 1, will remove a layer of management. In the new structure, each product program will be led by a executive chief engineer who will report directly to Parks. Each engineer will lead a vehicle from inception to production and track costs, quality and the competitive landscape. Previously, each vehicle program was led by three people a vehicle line executive, director and chief engineer.Â 
